# Create a stacked bar chart in Python using Matplotlib, Seaborn to show the distribution of diet types within each region.

region_diet_counts = df.groupby(['region', 'diet']).size().unstack().fillna(0)
region_diet_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, color=['green', 'red'], figsize=(10, 6))
plt.xlabel('Region')
plt.ylabel('Count of Dishes')
plt.title('Distribution of Diet Types Within Each Region')
plt.legend(title='Diet Type')
plt.show()

#Create a scatter plot in Python using Matplotlib to visualize the relationship between preparation time and cooking time, with different colors for vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes (vegetarian=green, non-vegetarian=red. Use grid)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
veg = df[df['diet'] == 'Vegetarian']
plt.scatter(veg['prep_time'], veg['cook_time'], color='green', label='Vegetarian')
non_veg = df[df['diet'] == 'Non-Vegetarian']
plt.scatter(non_veg['prep_time'], non_veg['cook_time'], color='red', label='Non-Vegetarian')
plt.xlabel('Preparation Time (minutes)')
plt.ylabel('Cooking Time (minutes)')
plt.title('Relationship Between Preparation Time and Cooking Time by Diet Type')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

#Create a pie chart in Python using Matplotlib to show the distribution of diet types, with a shadow effect and a custom start angle, with one slice (non-vegetarian) exploded.

#Donut chart - create a donut chart in Python using Matplotlib to show the distribution of diet types.
# Sample data
diet_counts = df['diet'].value_counts()

# Custom colors
colors = ['#ff9999','#66b3ff']

# Create a pie chart
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
plt.pie(diet_counts, labels=diet_counts.index, colors=colors, startangle=140, autopct='%1.1f%%')

# Draw a circle at the center of the pie to create a donut
centre_circle = plt.Circle((0,0),0.70,fc='white')
fig = plt.gcf()
fig.gca().add_artist(centre_circle)

# Equal aspect ratio ensures that pie is drawn as a circle.
plt.title('Distribution of Diet Types (Donut Chart)')
plt.show()

#Create a box plot in Python using Matplotlib to visualize the distribution of preparation times for vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes, with custom colors for each box (use medianprops, boxprops and try some other functions as well)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

# Custom properties
boxprops = dict(color="blue", linewidth=2)
medianprops = dict(color="red", linewidth=2)
whiskerprops = dict(color="green", linewidth=2)
capprops = dict(color="black", linewidth=2)

# Plot vegetarian
veg_prep_time = df[df['diet'] == 'Vegetarian']['prep_time']
non_veg_prep_time = df[df['diet'] == 'Non-Vegetarian']['prep_time']

plt.boxplot([veg_prep_time, non_veg_prep_time], labels=['Vegetarian', 'Non-Vegetarian'],
            boxprops=boxprops, medianprops=medianprops, whiskerprops=whiskerprops, capprops=capprops)

plt.xlabel('Diet Type')
plt.ylabel('Preparation Time (minutes)')
plt.title('Distribution of Preparation Times by Diet Type')
plt.show()
